  "instructions": [
    "Heat the tandoor clay pot over high heat until it reaches 450°F.",
    "Add 1 tablespoon of sesame oil to the pot and swirl it around to coat the bottom.",
    "Add the chicken to the pot and cook for 5 minutes, or until browned on all sides.",
    "Add the garlic, ginger, and onion to the pot and cook for 2 minutes, or until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the bell peppers, snow peas, and soy sauce to the pot and cook for 3 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender-crisp.",
    "Stir in the tahini, Gochujang, and rice vinegar. Cook for 1 minute, or until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Season the stir-fry with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the X-tra Spicy Wok-Seared American Chicken Stir-fry hot, garnished with sliced green onions and sesame seeds if desired."
  ],
